<br>
Besides, Arnold is going to be a huge failure as the Governor of California.  Structurally, California has enormous, intractable problems, and they are not susceptible to easy fixes.  That's why many Republican strategists believe that it wasn't in President Bush's interest to have a Republican as Governor of California, because they are pretty certain he can't succeed and they don't want to have his failure attributed to the Republicans in general, or to President Bush more specifically.  That's why the White House took a very hands off position with respect to the recall race.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sippin7>Sippin7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:yellow;'>Tavern Ale Swiller</span></span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(10/8/03 6:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3589.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ahnuld for pres in 2008?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Besides, Arnold is going to be a huge failure as the Governor of California. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
